Senegal concluded their World Cup preparations with a 2-0 victory over South Korea. Kim Young-Gwon’s 67th-minute own goal put the Lions ahead in the friendly, which was played behind closed doors in Austria. Amiens forward Moussa Konate wrapped up the victory with a stoppage-time penalty as Aliou Cisse’s side warmed up for Group H clashes with Poland, Japan and Colombia in style. Attention now turns to the start of this summer’s tournament in Russia, where South Korea, drawn alongside Germany, Sweden and Mexico, have their work cut out getting out of Group F. 